## Conventions for this template

- Quote each reviewer comment **verbatim** in a block-quote. Don't paraphrase — the editor needs to see what was raised, in their words.
- Number responses as `<reviewer>.<comment>` — Reviewer 1's third comment is `1.3`. Lets you reference back ("see response 2.1").
- Every response ends with a **change made** line. Either points to a specific location (section/paragraph/line) or explicitly says "No change made because [reason]". No silent skips.
- Keep responses short. The editor reads many of these; respect their time. Long context belongs in the manuscript, not the response letter.
- A render command (planned for ThesisStudio v1.1) will extract a journal-ready response letter from this structured tracker. Until then, copy-paste into your journal's submission system manually.
